<p>On my test server, I installed a newer version of openssl...</p>  <pre><code>#openssl version OpenSSL 0.9.8h 28 May 2008  #./config --prefix=/usr --openssldir=/usr/local/openssl enable-tlsext shared  #make #make test #make install #mv /usr/bin/openssl /root/ #ln -s /usr/local/ssl/bin/openssl /usr/bin/openssl  #openssl version    OpenSSL 1.0.1g 7 Apr 2014 </code></pre>  <p>Then I reinstalled apache (same version that I had) to get it to work with the newer version of openssl.</p>  <pre><code>#./configure  --prefix=/usr/local/apache-2.2.10 \ --enable-ssl \ --with-ssl=/usr/local/openssl \ --enable-ssl-staticlib-deps \ --enable-mods-static=ssl #make #make test #make install #ln -s /usr/local/apache-2.2.10 /usr/local/apache  </code></pre>  <p>I then restarted Apache. When I go to my phpinfo() file, it shows the old version of openssl: SSL_VERSION_LIBRARY - OpenSSL/0.9.8h</p>